## Issue Details
- **ID:** PAN-388
- **Title:** vBRIEF integration: structured plans → programmatic beads → DAG visualization
- **URL:** https://github.com/eltmon/panopticon-cli/issues/388

## Description
## Summary

Integrate the [vBRIEF v0.5 spec](https://github.com/deftai/vBRIEF) as the structured plan format for Panopticon's planning pipeline. vBRIEF is an open specification for structured planning documents with DAG dependency modeling.

The core idea: **the planning agent thinks once into a structured vBRIEF plan, then everything downstream is mechanical** — beads creation, dependency ordering, visualization, and Cloister scheduling are all derived from the plan without additional LLM tokens.

## Current Pipeline

```
Planning agent → freeform PRD.md + STATE.md + LLM-generated bd create calls
```

Problems:
- PRD is freeform markdown — not machine-parseable
- Beads tasks are generated independently by the LLM (can drift from the plan)
- No dependency graph — beads are flat, Cloister can't reason about ordering
- Each `bd create` costs LLM tokens for something that could be mechanical

## Target Pipeline

```
Planning agent → vBRIEF plan.json (structured, with DAG edges)
                    ↓
              vbrief-to-beads converter (programmatic, zero LLM tokens)
                    ↓
              beads with dependencies
                    ↓
              Cloister reads DAG → smart task scheduling
                    ↓
              Dashboard renders interactive plan viewer + dependency graph
```

## Phases

### Phase 1: Plan generation (PAN-386) ✅
- [x] Planning agent outputs `.planning/plan.vbrief.json` alongside PRD.md
- [x] Beads upgraded to Dolt backend (v0.62.0)
- [x] Gate checks use `bd list --json` instead of `existsSync(issues.jsonl)`

### Phase 2: vBRIEF TypeScript library + programmatic beads ✅ partial
- [x] `src/lib/vbrief/` — Types, builder (fluent API), validator (schema + DAG cycle detection), I/O utilities
- [x] `createBeadsFromVBrief()` converter: reads plan.vbrief.json, creates beads programmatically
  - Maps `items[].id` → bead title with issue label
  - Maps `items[].metadata.difficulty` → difficulty label
  - Maps `items[].priority` → bead priority
  - Maps `edges` with `type: "blocks"` → `bd dep add`
  - Maps `items[].narrative` → bead description
- [x] `topologicalOrder()`, `getUnblockedItems()`, `getBlockers()` — DAG query utilities
- [ ] Planning agent stops calling `bd create` directly — converter handles it
- [ ] Token savings: eliminates LLM-generated shell commands for task creation

### Phase 3: Plan viewer + DAG visualization
- [ ] Dashboard component renders vBRIEF plan as interactive dependency graph
  - ReactFlow (same library as vBRIEF Studio)
  - Status colors per node (pending/running/completed/blocked)
  - Edge types visually distinct (solid=blocks, dashed=informs)
- [ ] Plan viewer panel: click workspace → see structured plan
  - Narratives (Problem, Constraint, Risk, Alternative)
  - Acceptance criteria with pass/fail status
  - Requirements with sub-items
- [ ] Click-through from graph node → item detail (narrative, acceptance criteria, bead status)
- [ ] Click-through from graph node → bead detail
- [ ] Live updates as agents close beads (vBRIEF item status syncs with bead status)

### Phase 4: Cloister DAG scheduling
- [ ] Cloister reads plan.vbrief.json edges to determine task readiness
- [ ] `blocks` edges prevent starting downstream tasks until upstream completes
- [ ] `informs` edges provide context ordering (soft preference, not hard gate)
- [ ] Auto-detect ready tasks: all `blocks` predecessors completed → task is schedulable
- [ ] Critical path detection for dashboard visibility
- [ ] Bidirectional status sync: as agents close beads, vBRIEF item status updates

## Out of Scope (separate issues)

- **TRON encoding** (PAN-399) — compact serialization for token efficiency. Deprioritized; evaluate Headroom (PAN-398) first as it provides deeper compression at the proxy level. Only do one or the other.
- **Hierarchical planning** (PAN-397) — Rally feature-level plans with story decomposition. Tracker-specific, orthogonal to the vBRIEF format itself.
- **Headroom integration** (PAN-398) — transparent context compression proxy. Subsumes TRON's value proposition at a deeper level.

## vBRIEF Format (v0.5)

```json
{
  "vBRIEFInfo": { "version": "0.5" },
  "plan": {
    "id": "PAN-XXX",
    "title": "Feature title",
    "status": "approved",
    "narratives": {
      "Problem": "...", "Proposal": "...",
      "Constraint": "...", "Risk": "...", "Alternative": "..."
    },
    "items": [
      { "id": "task-id", "title": "...", "status": "pending",
        "priority": "high", "metadata": { "difficulty": "medium" },
        "subItems": [
          { "id": "task-id.ac1", "title": "Acceptance criterion", "status": "pending",
            "metadata": { "kind": "acceptance_criterion" } }
        ] }
    ],
    "edges": [
      { "from": "task-a", "to": "task-b", "type": "blocks" }
    ]
  }
}
```

Edge types: `blocks` (hard dep), `informs` (soft), `invalidates` (conditional), `suggests` (weak)

## References

- vBRIEF spec: https://github.com/deftai/vBRIEF
- vBRIEF Studio (visual editor): https://vbrief-studio.fly.dev
- Studio uses ReactFlow under the hood
